[I] A tool for creating benchmark-driven backend libraries

[T] Tensile is a tool for creating benchmark-driven backend libraries for
[T] GEMMs, GEMM-like problems (such as batched GEMM), and general N-dimensional
[T] tensor contractions on a GPU. The Tensile library is mainly used as backend
[T] library to rocBLAS.

[U] https://github.com/ROCm/Tensile

